# Global CO₂ Emissions Analysis (1992–2022)

This project explores global carbon dioxide (CO₂) and greenhouse gas emissions using publicly available data from [Our World in Data](https://github.com/owid/co2-data). It analyzes emission trends, identifies top emitters, and uncovers relationships between emissions, population, GDP, energy consumption, and temperature change. The project also investigates decoupling dynamics between economic growth and emissions.

---

## Dataset Overview

- **Source**: [OWID CO₂ Dataset](https://github.com/owid/co2-data)  
- **Format**: CSV  
- **Rows**: ~50,000  
- **Columns**: 79  
- **Key Variables**:  
  - `country`: Country or region name  
  - `year`: Year of observation  
  - `co2`: Total CO₂ emissions (million tonnes)  
  - `co2_per_capita`: Emissions per person  
  - `gdp`: Gross Domestic Product (USD)  
  - `population`: Total population  
  - `primary_energy_consumption`: Total energy use  
- **Time Range**: Covers historical data from 1750 to the most recent year available (typically 2022); analysis focuses on 1992–2022

