## Key Insights

- Strong correlation (r = 0.82) between CO₂ emissions and temperature change  
- Top emitters in recent decades: China, United States, India, Russia  
- Fossil-fuel economies (e.g., Japan, South Korea, Italy) show nearly pure CO₂ emissions profiles  
- Agriculture and land-use economies (e.g., India, Brazil, Indonesia) emit higher shares of methane and nitrous oxide  
- Mixed industrial economies (e.g., United States, China, Europe) are CO₂-dominant but methane and N₂O emissions are non-trivial  
- Decoupling is rare but visible — some economies are beginning to bend the curve

